Some species accept a variety of large leaves (monocot and dicot) while others seem to be more restricted to certain taxa, such as palm (
Arecaceae
) or aroid (
Araceae
) leaves. During the day, the spiders press their bodies and legs against the leaf in a very cryptic resting position, with the prolateral sides of the legs close to the leaf surface (
Figs 17
, 
127
). Unforced activity was only seen at night (
Fig. 133
).
